answer.p:
 We solve
				 c_1\vec{1  1} + c_2\vec{-1  1} = \vec{1  2}
				with


					\amat{
					 1  -1  1 ;
               				1  1   2
					}
					\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
					&\amat{
					 1  -1  1;
               				0  2   1
					}


				and conclude that c_2=\frac{1}{2} and so c_1=\frac{3}{2}.
